# BrandOS — Product Requirements Document
**For Claude Code. Read this fully before writing any code.**

---

## 1. What this product is

BrandOS is an AI-powered content platform for internal content marketers at multi-brand enterprise organisations (e.g. a content marketer at Galeries Lafayette Group who manages brands like BHV Marais, La Redoute, etc.).

The core problem: AI tools have no memory of brand voice. Every session starts blank. A marketer managing 4–8 brands must manually re-explain tone, vocabulary, audience, and guardrails every time they use AI — for every brand, every day.

The solution: BrandOS stores each brand's voice kit once. Campaign briefs arrive via tagged Gmail emails. The AI extracts the brief, the user confirms it, and content is generated in the correct brand voice in 1–2 iterations — without re-explaining anything.

**Two outputs only in V1:** LinkedIn post and blog post.

---

## 2. User persona

- Internal content marketer at a multi-brand conglomerate
- Manages 4–8 distinct brands under one parent company
- Uses AI daily but gets generic output because AI has no brand memory
- Not technical. Moderate AI comfort.
- Primary pain: re-explaining brand context every session, copy-pasting briefs from email into AI tools
- B2B enterprise user — willing to fill detailed forms, goes through formal evaluation (RFP/sandbox), cares about output quality and pricing above all else

---

## 3. Tech stack decisions

- **Frontend:** React + Tailwind CSS
- **Backend:** Node.js / Express
- **Database:** PostgreSQL (brand kits, users, inbox cards, drafts)
- **AI:** Anthropic Claude API (claude-sonnet-4-6) for all extraction and generation
- **Email integration:** Gmail API — reactive pull model (user applies Gmail label, system reads only labelled messages)
- **Auth:** SSO primary via Okta/OneLogin/SAML 2.0. Google Workspace OAuth as second option. Work email + password as fallback.
- **File storage:** S3 or equivalent for PDF/DOCX brand guideline uploads
- **Deployment:** Vercel (frontend) + Railway or Render (backend)

---

## 4. Architecture overview

```
User tags Gmail message with "BrandOS — [Brand Name]" label
  → Gmail webhook fires to BrandOS backend
  → AI extraction pipeline runs on message content
  → Extracted fields stored as InboxCard in DB
  → Card appears in Brand Updates Inbox in UI

User selects card → confirms brief (G2) → previews content structure (G3)
  → Generation pipeline runs with brand kit + brief context
  → LinkedIn post + blog post generated in one pass
  → Output shown in tabbed workspace (G5)
  → User iterates via natural language bar
  → Exports via copy to clipboard
```

