## 7. Generation prompt architecture (5 layers)

Every generation call assembles context in this order:

```
Layer 1 — Brand identity (auto-loaded from brand_kit)
  Voice adjectives, vocabulary to use, restricted words (hard guardrail),
  channel rules for target format, content goal, publishing frequency

Layer 2 — Few-shot examples (from brand_kit.past_content_examples)
  1–3 real examples that already sound like the brand
  Strongest voice signal — weight this heavily in the system prompt

Layer 3 — Campaign brief (from G2 confirmed fields)
  Campaign type, audience, audience type, tone shift, key message,
  funnel stage, proof style, content role, CTA intent, deadline

Layer 4 — Preview edits (from G3 edited sections)
  Any sections the user edited in the preview screen
  These override the AI's free generation for those sections

Layer 5 — Channel format spec
  LinkedIn: max 220 words, hook in line 1, max 3 hashtags, no em dashes
  Blog: target word count based on frequency (daily=400, weekly=700, monthly=1000),
        subheadings optional, must end with a question if goal=thought_leadership
```

**Restricted words are enforced as a hard constraint, not a soft preference.** After generation, run a post-processing check. If any restricted word appears, regenerate automatically (once). Flag to user if it appears again.

