## 15. Confidence scoring implementation notes

The scoring runs entirely in the backend. The UI never shows a percentage.

```javascript
const FIELD_WEIGHTS = {
  key_message: 0.25,
  campaign_type: 0.20,
  audience: 0.20,
  tone_shift: 0.15,
  content_goal: 0.15,
  cta_intent: 0.05
};

// Per-field confidence scoring rules:
// - Explicitly stated in message: 0.85–1.0
// - Clearly inferable from context: 0.60–0.84
// - Ambiguous or absent: 0.0–0.59
// - No source quote found: cap at 0.60 regardless of LLM output

// Overall score
const overall = Object.entries(FIELD_WEIGHTS)
  .reduce((sum, [field, weight]) => sum + (field_scores[field] * weight), 0);

// Tiers (used internally for card ordering and refresh recommendation)
// High: overall >= 0.75
// Partial: overall >= 0.40
// Low: overall < 0.40

// UI representation:
// High: all chips green
// Partial: some chips amber/grey
// Low: most chips grey + advisory text on card
```

