## 16. Gmail API integration notes

**Required OAuth scopes (minimal):**
- `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.labels` — read label names
- `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.readonly` — read messages with specific labels

**Do NOT request:**
- Full gmail.modify or gmail.compose — unnecessary and will alarm enterprise IT

**Webhook setup:**
- Use Gmail Push Notifications via Google Cloud Pub/Sub
- Subscribe to mailbox changes for the specific label only
- On notification: fetch message, run extraction, store InboxCard

**Alternative (simpler for MVP):**
- Poll the labelled mailbox every 5 minutes via cron
- Less real-time but avoids Pub/Sub setup complexity
- Acceptable for MVP given typical enterprise usage patterns

**Label format:** `BrandOS — [Brand Name]`
Users create this label in Gmail manually. Instructions shown in settings/inbox setup screen.

